    <introduction>
      <para>
        This topic shows hot to setup 
        a testing environment on each supported platform.
      </para>
    </introduction>
    <section address="sectionWindowsPlatforms">
      <title>Windows platforms</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          Download and install the latest .NET Core SDK from
          <externalLink>
            <linkText>here</linkText>
            <linkUri>https://github.com/dotnet/core</linkUri>
          </externalLink>.
          From a shell of your choice, change the current directory to folder 
          <externalLink>
            <linkText>
              Novacta.Analytics.Tests
            </linkText>
            <linkUri>https://github.com/novacta/analytics/blob/master/tests/Novacta.Analytics.Tests</linkUri>
          </externalLink>
          and execute the following command:
        </para>
        <code language="none" title="Running tests">
          dotnet test
        </code>
        <para>
          The console outputs showing
          reports in which is signaled if the corresponding tests were successful.
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>
    <section address="sectionNonWindowsPlatforms">
      <title>Linux and macOS platforms</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          Download and install the latest .NET Core SDK from
          <externalLink>
            <linkText>here</linkText>
            <linkUri>https://github.com/dotnet/core</linkUri>
          </externalLink>.
          From a shell of your choice, change the current directory to folder
          <externalLink>
            <linkText>
              Novacta.Analytics.Tests
            </linkText>
            <linkUri>https://github.com/novacta/analytics/blob/master/tests/Novacta.Analytics.Tests</linkUri>
          </externalLink>
          and execute the following two commands:
        </para>
        <code language="none" title="Preparing Linux or macOS environments for tests">
          export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=.
        </code>
        <code language="none" title="Running tests">
          dotnet test
        </code>
        <para>
          The console outputs showing
          reports in which is signaled if the corresponding tests were successful.
        </para>
      </content>
    </section>
